 aside from {{stat|Speed}}. While Drampa is exclusive to [[Pokémon Sun and Moon|Moon]] and [[Pokémon Ultra Sun and Ultra Moon|Ultra Moon]], Turtonator is exclusive to Pokémon Sun and Ultra Sun.\n** In addition, Drampa and Turtonator both have the lowest base {{stat|Speed}} stat of all {{type|Dragon}} Pokémon.\n* Drampa was designed by [[Hitoshi Ariga]].\n* Drampa is tied with {{p|Porygon-Z}} and {{me|Pidgeot}} for the highest base {{stat|Special Attack}} stat of all {{type|Normal}} Pokémon.\n\n===Origin===\nDrampa appears to be based on a {{wp|Chinese dragon}}, such as the {{wp|Zhulong (mythology)|Zhulong}} (torch dragon), a mythological creature with the face of an old man and the body of a {{wp|dragon}}.\n\n====Name origin====\nDrampa may be a combination of \'\'dragon\'\' and \'\'grampa\'\' (a variation on \'\'grandpa\'\').\n\nJijilong may be a combination of 爺 \'\'jijī\'\' (informal term for old man) and 龍 \'\'lóng\'\' (Chinese for dragon).\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Normal|type2=Dragon\n|ja=ジジーロン \'\'Jijilong\'\'|jameaning=From {{tt|爺 \'\'jijī\'\'|informal term for old man}} and {{tt|龍 \'\'lóng\'\'|Chinese for dragon}}\n|fr=Draïeul|frmeaning=From \'\'dragon\'\' and {{tt|\'\'aïeul\'\'|elder, ancestor}}\n|es=Drampa|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Sen-Long|demeaning=From \'\'Senior\'\' and {{tt|神龍 / 神龙 \'\'shénlóng\'\'|dragon from Chinese mythology}}\n|it=Drampa|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=할비롱 \'\'Halbirong\'\'|komeaning=From {{tt|할아버지 \'\'harabeoji\'\'|grandfather}} and {{tt|龍 \'\'lóng\'\'|Chinese for dragon}}\n|zh_cmn=老翁龍 / 老翁龙 \'\'Lǎowēnglóng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|老翁 \'\'lǎowēng\'\'|old man}} and {{tt|龍 \'\'lóng\'\'|dragon}}\n|zh_yue=老翁龍 \'\'Lóuhyūnglùhng\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|老翁 \'\'lóuhyūng\'\'|old man}} and {{tt|龍 \'\'lùhng\'\'|dragon}}\n|ru=Дрампа \'\'Drampa\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name}}\n{{-}}\n\n==Related articles==\n* [[Grandpa Forest]]\n\n==Notes==\n<references/>\n==External links==\n{{Pokém